snippet: An active Alan Gilbert led the New York Philharmonic in two Nielsen concertos, one for flute and one for violin, and Tchaikovsky’s Second Symphony on Wednesday.
abstract: Zachary Woolfe reviews performance by the New York Philharmonic, featuring violinist Nikolaj Znaider and conducted by Alan Gilbert, at Avery Fisher Hall.
lead_paragraph: An active Alan Gilbert led the New York Philharmonic in two Nielsen concertos, one for flute and one for violin, and Tchaikovsky’s Second Symphony on Wednesday.

headline.seo: New York Philharmonic Performs Carl Nielsen’s Works
headline.main: Shifting Moods on a Vigorous Trip Embracing Nielsen and Tchaikovsky
